WHO   — XBOX 360 — an exereunesis sphere — the teardown
WHAT  — Microsoft's second console led the HD generation with a triple-core PowerPC CPU and an ATI GPU that pioneered unified shaders. Fast, online-first, and developer-friendly, it was nearly derailed by the 'Red Ring of Death' — one of the most infamous hardware-reliability failures in console history.
WHERE — the teardown — a made machine, opened and explored  Framework inputs: the chips; the buses; the spec; the lore  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
